# krome_init_abund.dat — initial species mixing ratios for krome_solve
#
# Used when INITAB=1 in the MARCS input file.
# Each line specifies a species name and its mixing ratio (n_i / n_total).
# Species names must match those in ./krome/MARCS_build/info.log exactly
# (same case, no trailing spaces).
# Species not listed here receive the default abundance (1E-20).
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# Format:  species_name   mixing_ratio
#
# Example Earth-like atmosphere (modify as needed):
N2        7.8000E-01
O2        2.1000E-01
Ar        9.3000E-03
CO2       4.0000E-04
H2O       1.0000E-02
CH4       1.7000E-06
N2O       3.2000E-07
O3        1.0000E-07
